'''AccuSystems LLC''' is an American company headquartered in [[Pueblo, Colorado]] that develops, licenses, supports, and sells [[document imaging]] software and [[electronic document management]], primarily to the banking and finance industries.<ref name="BankNews - Info">{{cite news|last=Scheibach|first=Michael|title=New Era of Document Management|url=http://www.banknews.com/Single-News-Page.51.0.html?&no_cache=1&tx_ttnews%5Bpointer%5D=8&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=16374&tx_ttnews%5BbackPid%5D=978&cHash=b5f84d6b88|accessdate=4 December 2013|newspaper=BankNews|date=May 2012}}</ref> Over 200 banks currently use AccuSystems' software.<ref name="Chieftain">{{cite news|last=Darrow |first=Dennis |title=Documented Success: Growing software firm helps banks track files |accessdate=4 December 2013 |newspaper=[[The Pueblo Chieftain]] |date=2010-11-14 |url=http://www.chieftain.com/business/local/article_2ef2e46e-ef83-11df-83ad-001cc4c03286.html |archivedate=January 10, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110051752/http://www.chieftain.com/business/local/article_2ef2e46e-ef83-11df-83ad-001cc4c03286.html }}</ref>
In 2002, AccuSystems made its first sale to [[People's United Bank|People's Bank]].<ref name=Chieftain />
